  113:5:2:"The second word of verse (113:5) is a masculine singular noun and is in the genitive case (<span class=\"at\">مجرور</span>). The noun's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">shīn rā rā</i> (<span class=\"at\">ش ر ر</span>)."
  113:5:3:"The third word of verse (113:5) is an indefinite masculine active participle and is in the genitive case (<span class=\"at\">مجرور</span>). The active participle's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">ḥā sīn dāl</i> (<span class=\"at\">ح س د</span>)."
  113:5:4:"The fourth word of verse (113:5) is a time adverb."
